The performance categorization is based on the following thresholds: 
- High: average response time > 2 seconds; 
- Moderate: average response time between 1 and 2 seconds; 
- Low: average response time < 1 second.

- High-quality scores refer to a data quality score greater than 0.7;
- 'zipping along' refers to an average response time less than 2.0 seconds;
- 'perfect status codes' refer to HTTP status codes of 200, indicating successful requests;
- 'crowning jewel' signifies the top-ranked dataset within each source based on quality score.

sql:
SELECT MIN(within_variation) AS min_within_variation, MIN(data_quality_score) AS min_data_quality_score
FROM datasets
WHERE hemisphere = (SELECT hemisphere_id FROM hemispheres WHERE hemisphere_name = 'Southern');
